The paper discusses energy consumption in parallel and distributed computing systems, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the use of dynamic voltage-frequency scaling (DVFS), which is a technique used in computer architecture and embedded systems, falling under the category of Architecture (cs.AR). The paper also involves optimization and algorithm design, which falls under the category of Systems and Control (cs.SY) and Performance (cs.PF). Finally, the paper involves the use of discrete frequencies in processors, which falls under the category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
